# ── Drafting model ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFAULT: GitHub Models — FREE with ANY GitHub account (no Student/Pro/Copilot
# needed, no credit card). Create a fine-grained token at
# https://github.com/settings/tokens with the "Models" account permission = read.
GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_...

# Which model writes the posts. Default openai/gpt-5-chat (most natural-sounding).
# Other free GitHub options: openai/gpt-5, meta/llama-3.3-70b-instruct, openai/gpt-4o-mini.
# MODEL=openai/gpt-5-chat

# ── Don't have / want GitHub? Use any OpenAI-compatible provider instead ──────
# Set these two and they override the GitHub default. Examples:
#   Ollama (free, local, no key):  AI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1   AI_API_KEY=ollama   MODEL=llama3.1
#   Groq (free tier, fast):        AI_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1   AI_API_KEY=gsk_...   MODEL=llama-3.3-70b-versatile
#   OpenRouter (free models):      AI_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1   AI_API_KEY=sk-or-...   MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free
#   OpenAI (paid):                 AI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1   AI_API_KEY=sk-...   MODEL=gpt-4o
# AI_BASE_URL=
# AI_API_KEY=

# ── X authentication (for scraping) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# RECOMMENDED: paste your X auth_token cookie here. This is the most reliable way
# (no automated login, no passkey problems). How to get it:
#   1. Log into X (x.com) in your NORMAL browser.
#   2. Open DevTools (F12) -> Application (Chrome) / Storage (Firefox) -> Cookies
#      -> https://x.com  ->  find the row named  auth_token  ->  copy its Value.
#   3. Paste it below.
# Use a throwaway account — scraping breaks X's ToS.
X_AUTH_TOKEN=
# Optional, only needed for some actions (copy the `ct0` cookie the same way):
# X_CT0=

# Alternative to the cookie: run `python main.py login` to sign in via a window.
# Posting is always done by hand — no X API keys needed.
